  "body": "This documents aims at discussing the opportunity of using an existing solution \r\nsuch as https://reactnavigation.org/ for react navigation logic.\r\n\r\nstatus: RFC\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- we are currently using our own navigation logic\r\n- we don't have transitions\r\n- we don't have documentation describing how things currently work\r\n- all 3 tab views always \"active\" so all subscriptions (~240!) are recalculated each time app-db is changed\r\n- no deep-linking\r\n\r\nWishlist:\r\n- better animation on navigation, offers transitions out of the box\r\n- animations should be fast/smooth\r\n- may need some lazy/deferred loading of components to make navigation faster\r\n- deep linking for notifications\r\n\r\nThings to determine for each candidate:\r\n- what are the advantages over the existing solution ?\r\n- which changes are required to use it in status-react ?\r\n- does the router hide its state internally ?\r\n- does it uses native transitions or relies on implementation in JS ?\r\n- opinion of the design team on the candidate\r\n\r\nPotential candidates so far:\r\n- https://reactnavigation.org/ (with re-frame example implementation here https://github.com/vikeri/re-navigate)\r\n- https://wix.github.io/react-native-navigation/\r\n- http://airbnb.io/native-navigation/",
